abstract: In a parody campaign ad on the Web, Elizabeth Warren, the Harvard professor who set up the consumer protection bureau and is now running for Senate in Massachusetts, is humorously portrayed as growing up on the "ragged edge of the middle class" and joining a gang at the age of 11. The spoof campaign ad called for a "revenge voucher" that would allow citizens to "kick anyone from Wall Street" in a, well, sensitive area. Warning: The faux Ms. Warren has a foul mouth, so viewer discretion is advised.
